data.chText: （就可能发生的意外等提出的）警告，警示；先兆
data.enText: a statement, an event, etc. telling sb that sth bad or unpleasant may happen in the future so that they can try to avoid it

data.chText: 医生发出警告不要吃在那条河里捕的鱼。
data.enText: Doctors issued a warning against eating any fish caught in the river.

data.chText: 就某事向某人发出充分的 / 预先的 / 足够的警告
data.enText: to give sb fair/advance/adequate warning of sth

data.chText: 那座桥在没有任何先兆的情况下坍塌了。

data.enText: Let me give you a word of warning .

data.chText: （就将要遭受的处罚等提出的）警告，警戒
data.enText: a statement telling sb that they will be punished if they continue to behave in a particular way

data.chText: 向某人发出口头 / 书面 / 最后警告
data.enText: to give sb a verbal/written/final warning

data.chText: 她没有理会警示前方危险的标志。
data.enText: She had ignored the warning signs of trouble ahead.
Police fired a number of warning shots .

data.chText: 当她的信原封不动被退回时，不祥之感就来了。
data.enText: Warning bells began to ring (= it was a sign that sth was wrong) when her letters were returned unopened.

means: (就可能发生的意外等提出的)警示
(就将要遭受的处罚等提出的)警告，警戒
提醒注意(可能发生的事)

tr: cautionary advice about something imminent (especially imminent danger or other unpleasantness)
example: a letter of admonition about the dangers of immorality
the warning was to beware of surprises
his final word of advice was not to play with matches

tr: notification of something, usually in advance
example: they gave little warning of their arrival
she had only had four days' warning before leaving Berlin
a warning that still more bombs could explode

value.def: A warning is something which is said or written to tell people of a possible danger, problem, or other unpleasant thing that might happen.

example.ex: The minister gave a warning that if war broke out, it would be catastrophic...
example.tran: 部长警告说，战争一旦爆发将会是灾难性的。

example.ex: He was killed because he ignored a warning to put stronger cords on his parachute...
example.tran: 他忽视了降落伞上要求使用更结实的绳索的警告信息，因而命丧黄泉。

example.ex: The government has unveiled new health warnings for cigarette packets.
example.tran: 政府公布了新的用于香烟盒上的健康警示语。

value.def: A warning is an advance notice of something that will happen, often something unpleasant or dangerous.

example.ex: The soldiers opened fire without warning...
example.tran: 士兵们在没有发出警告的情况下开了枪。

example.ex: With no warning, he was fired from his job...
example.tran: 他没有受到任何警告，就被解雇了。

example.ex: At the White House, U.S. officials said they had some advance warning of the coup attempt.
example.tran: 在白宫，美国官员们说他们曾事先接到政变警告。

value.def: Warning actions or signs give a warning.

example.tran: 她忽视了一些预警信号。

example.ex: Some fog warning signs had been put up with flashing yellow lights.
example.tran: 一些配有黄色闪光灯的大雾警示标志立了起来。

trans: 预先警报制度，预警制（度）；预先通知制
警示灯；警示燈；警告灯；警报灯；报警信号灯
报警报文；报警信息；警告消息
